<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Understanding Gender Inequality</h1>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <a href="#causes">Causes</a>
        <a href="#effects">Effects</a>
        <a href="#solutions">Solutions</a>
    </nav>

    <section id="introduction">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>Gender inequality refers to the social phenomenon where individuals are treated differently based on their gender, often leading to unequal opportunities, resources, and rights. Despite progress in recent years, this issue persists in many aspects of life, including education, employment, and health.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="causes">
        <h2>Causes of Gender Inequality</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Cultural Norms:</strong> Societal expectations often define roles based on gender.</li>
            <li><strong>Lack of Education:</strong> Limited access to education for women in some regions exacerbates inequality.</li>
            <li><strong>Economic Disparities:</strong> Wage gaps and employment opportunities are often skewed in favor of men.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="effects">
        <h2>Effects of Gender Inequality</h2>
        <p>Gender inequality negatively impacts individuals and society, leading to:</p>
        <div class="stats">
            <div>
                <h3>Poverty</h3>
                <p>Women are more likely to experience poverty due to wage disparities and limited opportunities.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>Health Disparities</h3>
                <p>Inadequate access to healthcare and nutrition affects women disproportionately.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>Economic Loss</h3>
                <p>Gender inequality reduces overall economic growth by limiting talent and labor participation.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="solutions">
        <h2>Solutions to Address Gender Inequality</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Promote equal access to education and training for all genders.</li>
            <li>Implement policies that ensure equal pay for equal work.</li>
            <li>Encourage the representation of women in leadership roles.</li>
            <li>Challenge and change discriminatory cultural norms.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Gender Equality Initiative</p>
